result.execSummary:
The defendant Dalton David Yauck was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Dalton David Yauck is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Dalton David Yauck was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Dalton David Yauck in court with attorney Mark Jay Gumz.  Defendant Dalton David Yauck in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Gumz states that there is a joint recommendation in the matter to Count 1.  
  Atty Hendee states plea agreement to Ct. 1.  Ct. 2 to be dismissed.  Atty Gumz agrees. Defendant agrees and enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct. 1.  Ct. 2 to be dismissed.

Atty Hendee makes sentencing recommendations.
Atty Gumz responds.

BY THE COURT:  Ct. 1:  Court orders 50 days in the Marquette County Jail
Credit = 38 days
Time Served
Court Costs = $243.00
DNA Sample + $200.00 Surcharge
  Defendant agrees to the $15.00 payment plan fee.
Payment Plan:  $50.00/month commencing in March
Ct. 2 to be dismissed.

**Defendant may be released

Defendant received a copy of the criminal complaint & waives it's reading.  Court advises defendant of right to an attorney.  Defendant wants to get an Attorney.
Court finds probable cause.

  BY THE COURT:  Court enters a Not Guilty plea on behalf of the defendant.
Set for Return.

Defendant Dalton David Yauck in court, in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Atty Hendee requests a $500 cash bond.  Atty Hendee states that the defendant has warrants out of Milwaukee County from August and October.
Court questions the defendant.  Defendant responds.

  BY THE COURT:  Court sets a $500 Cash bond with conditions:
*No special conditions

  Return date scheduled for January 7, 2016 at 01:45 pm.
